channel.title: Final_Devolution 2.7; Silabsoft Clients
channel.description:
[center]Currently, majority of my projects are based with Final_Devolution 2.7; It's clean and I have finally gotten used to not using the leechfest of deltascape. But at the moment I want to make a silabsoft server, to try and see how far I can go with just a server; no clients.
I am given this error upon login
[code]Error: T2 - 126,126,126 - 13,0,0 - 64,121,101,108,64,68,97,110,99,101,10,72,127,[/code]
Anybody here have a few quick steps to make it compatible? Because not only do I want to fix this, some of my friends do, thanks in advance[/center]
